T1  - Transmission of external price disturbances and the composition of trade
AU  - Katseli-Papaefstratiou, Louka T.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 10
IS  - 3
SP  - 357
EP  - 375
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/08/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(80)90016-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199680900161
AB  - This paper focuses on the role of trade composition in the transmission of external price disturbances. It is shown that the effects of an increase in the price of imports on domestic prices and the trade balance crucially depend on the cross price elasticity of demand in the case of final goods and the elasticity of substitution between factors in the case of intermediate goods. In the case of an input such as oil, where the elasticity of substitution between imported and domestic factors of production is less than unity, an increase in its price will give rise to a balance-of-trade deficit but will have ambiguous effects on domestic prices.
ER  - 

